Pre-Game Insights: The 5th ODI match of the Australia Tour of England 2024 will see England take on Australia at County Ground, Bristol, on September 29, 2024, at 3:30 PM IST.
After a successful comeback from England, having won 2 consecutive games over Australia by dominating them with his all-round attack they pushed the Aussies on the back foot.
Now the series is equal at 2-2, and fans await a thrilling action in the final ODI match on 29th September to determine who will win the series.
The County Ground in Bristol is known for being a batsman-friendly pitch, providing good speed and bounce that encourage stroke play, this ground has seen an even battle between the bat and ball.

The weather forecast indicates rain, with a temperature of 14°C. There is an 80% chance of precipitation, accompanied by a humidity level of 78%. Additionally, expect wind speeds of 34 km/h throughout the day.
England Predicted Playing 11: Philip Salt, Ben Duckett, Will Jacks, Harry Brook (c), Jamie Smith (wk), Liam Livingstone, Jacob Bethell, Brydon Carse, Jofra Archer, Matthew Potts, Adil Rashid
Australia Predicted Playing 11: Travis Head, Mitchell Marsh (c), Steven Smith, Josh Inglis (wk), Marnus Labuschagne, Alex Carey, Glenn Maxwell, Sean Abbott, Mitchell Starc, Adam Zampa, Josh Hazlewood
Looking at the squad strength and previous performance, England are looking stronger and are the favorites to win the game.
